author: CNN
description:
Trump ally Charlie Kirk was shot at an event in Utah, a source familiar with the matter says.

The extent of Kirk’s injuries were not immediately clear. #CNN #News
title: Source: Conservative activist Charlie Kirk shot during event in Utah

author: CNN
description:
Israel is facing growing condemnation after it attacked Hamas leadership in the capital of Qatar, a US ally and key mediator in Gaza ceasefire talks — putting hostage negotiations at risk.  Hamas said the strike killed five members but failed to kill the negotiating delegation, the target of the strikes. Doubts are now emerging about the success of the attack, according to two Israeli officials. President Donald Trump has criticized the strike, saying that by the time his administration learned of the attack and told the Qataris, there was little he could do to stop it.

CNN's Bianna Golodryga speaks with Amit Segal, chief political commentator for Israel's Channel 12 News, who offers a theory on how Hamas officials may have survived the targeted attack. #CNN #News
title: Families of hostages react to Israeli strike in Qatar

author: CNN
description: Venezuela is not seeking a military confrontation with the United States or any other regional actor, its Foreign Minister Yván Gil told CNN in a rare interview, as tensions rise with Washington, including over the recent deadly US Navy strike on a vessel allegedly carrying drugs in the Caribbean.  #CNN #News
title: Exclusive: Top Venezuelan official speaks out about US attack on alleged drug boat

author: CNN
description:
The Polish deputy prime minister says Russian President Vladimir Putin is mocking President Donald Trump’s peace efforts and testing NATO after fighter jets shot down multiple Russian drones that violated Polish airspace.

CNN's Wolf Blitzer and Pamela Brown speak with Polish deputy prime minister and foreign minister Radosław Sikorski.

 #CNN #News
title: Poland shoots down Russian drones: 'This is an act of aggression'

author: CNN
description: CNN's Jeremy Diamond breaks down the prospect of a ceasefire in Gaza after an Israeli attack on Hamas leadership in Qatar. Hamas said the strike killed five members but failed to kill the negotiating delegation, the target of the strikes. #cnn #news
title: Analysis: What next for Gaza ceasefire after Qatar attack?

author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump’s strategy to ‘Make America Healthy Again’ includes investigating vaccine injuries and pharmaceutical practices but stops short of new regulatory action, for now.

US Health and Human Services Secretary Robert F. Kennedy Jr. unveiled the MAHA strategy on Tuesday, joined by Agriculture Department Secretary Brooke Rollins, Environmental Protection Agency Administrator Lee Zeldin, and other top Trump officials.

CNN's Kate Bolduan speaks with FDA commissioner Dr. Marty Makary. #CNN #News
title: 'We think the government is not your doctor': FDA commissioner on RFK Jr. MAHA report

author: CNN
description:
US inflation cooled off at the wholesale level in August, bolstering hopes that high tariffs aren’t yet causing prices to spiral out of control, fresh data showed Wednesday.

However, economists caution, the better-than-expected reading could be a sign of a slowing economy and that shrinking businesses’ margins could foretell higher prices for consumers in the near future.

CNN's Matt Egan reports, and John Berman speaks with former Yahoo Finance columnist Rick Newman. #CNN #News
title: Inflation for US producers cooled down in August

author: CNN
description: The Department of Justice seized the Amadea, a 348-foot megayacht, in Fiji in 2022 as part of task force effort to hold Russians friendly to the Kremlin accountable after its invasion of Ukraine. US prosecutors allege its owner, Suleiman Kerimov, who made his fortune in gold, violated US sanctions by using the US banking system to cover expenses for the vessel. The government is now auctioning off the boat to the highest bidder. CNN’s Kara Scannell reports. #cnn #news #yacht #doj
title: Look inside a megayacht seized from a Russian oligarch by the DOJ

author: CNN
description: NATO fighter jets shot down multiple Russian drones that violated Polish airspace during an attack on neighboring Ukraine early on Wednesday, as the military alliance denounced Moscow for “absolutely dangerous” behavior that ratcheted up tensions to a new level. Addressing the Polish parliament, Prime Minister Donald Tusk said that while there was no reason to say that Poland was in a state of war, it was closer to a conflict than any time since World War II. CNN’s Nick Paton Walsh reports. #CNN #News
title: Poland’s leader speaks out about Russia’s ‘large-scale provocation’

author: CNN
description: In an excerpt from her upcoming memoir, "107 Days," former Vice President Kamala Harris writes about former President Joe Biden's reelection decision, calling it reckless. CNN Senior Reporter Edward-Isaac Dovere explains why this is such a departure from her past remarks. #cnn #news
title: Kamala Harris calls Joe Biden's reelection decision reckless

author: CNN
description: Producers for a Broadway revival of “Cabaret” have announced that the show will be shutting down on September 21 after its leading man, Billy Porter, contracted a life threatening condition.
title: Billy Porter’s serious illness forces Broadway show to close

description: CNN's Kaitlan Collins interviews Sen. Bernie Sanders (I-VT) about health policy and the NYC mayoral race. #CNN #News

author: CNN
description:
CNN and Rotten Tomatoes picked 25 top-ranked shows about where we work:
Our workspaces are full of trials, tribulations and secret romances, all perfect fodder for good television. Jacqueline Coley, Rotten Tomatoes Awards Editor, explains how we landed on our ranking of 25 exceptional workplace shows and highlights two standouts. Find the rest at cnn.com/25workplaces   #cnn  #theofficeus #rottentomatoes  #severance #abbottelementary
title: Exceptional TV series about where we work

author: CNN
description: Overnight, Russian drone debris rained down on Poland as NATO jets scrambled to intercept them. Civilian buildings were damaged in the incursion, which Prime Minister Donald Tusk said brings he country “the closest we have been to open conflict since World War II.”
title: Poland PM: Closest to open conflict since World War II

author: CNN
description: After a historic Gen-Z led protest in Kathmandu, Nepal, that saw government buildings destroyed, the country's Prime Minister resign and at least 22 people killed, CNN spoke to eyewitnesses of the demonstrations who were on the ground. #CNN #news
title: Eyewitnesses describe Nepal protests

author: CNN
description: CNN chief data analyst Harry Enten looks at the New York City mayoral race and examines frontrunner Zohran Mamdani's popularity. #CNN #News
title: ‘How is Mamdani winning?’: Harry Enten breaks down the NYC mayoral race

author: CNN
description: Just three nautical miles off the coast of Pembrokeshire in Wales, Thorne Island is home to a 19th-century fort turned luxury home — complete with a helipad, rooftop bar, and space for 20 guests. Now, it’s on the market for $4 million. #cnn #news
title: Private island fort for sale

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump says he's unhappy about Israel's strikes inside Qatar targeting Hamas leaders. #CNN #News
title: Trump reacts to Israel’s strike in Qatar

author: CNN
description:
Doubts are emerging over the success of an Israeli strike that targeted Hamas leaders in Doha on Tuesday, according to two Israeli officials. 

The strike targeted Hamas’ chief negotiator Khalil al-Hayya and others, but Hamas did not list Al-Hayya among the dead. Hamas said the strike failed to assassinate their negotiating delegation, instead killing five lower-ranking members, including Al-Hayya’s son and his office director. #CNN #News
title: Doubts emerge over success of strike targeting Hamas leaders in Doha, Israeli officials say

author: CNN
description: CNN's Manu Raju asked Republican lawmakers about Donald Trump allegedly writing Jeffrey Epstein a lewd birthday letter in 2003. Trump denied writing and signing the letter. #cnn #news #politics
title: GOP lawmakers react to Epstein letter with Trump’s alleged signature

author: CNN
description: A vaccine used to treat chlamydia in Australia’s koala population has been approved for rollout in a world-first project. Researchers from the University of the Sunshine Coast spent more than 10 years developing the single-dose vaccine to protect the famed Australian marsupial from the effects of chlamydia, which is responsible for half of koala deaths in the country’s wild populations. #CNN #News
title: Koalas get first chlamydia vaccine

author: CNN
description: Jeffrey Epstein survivor Haley Robson speaks with CNN's Erin Burnett about President Donald Trump's dismissal of the Epstein birthday letter as "a dead issue." #CNN #News
title: Epstein survivor to Trump: 'Your first mistake was assuming that you knew your voters'

author: CNN
description:
“In retrospect,” Kamala Harris writes of letting Joe and Jill Biden decide on their own whether the then-president should have tried to run for re-election, “I think it was recklessness.” 

That is the assessment that the former vice president makes in her forthcoming memoir of her abbreviated 2024 run, in a significant break from the dutiful stance she took toward her old boss throughout their time in office and since.  #CNN #News
title: Kamala Harris says it was reckless to let Biden make reelection decision on his own

author: CNN
description:
Poland’s military said early Wednesday that it had shot down drones that violated its airspace during a Russian attack on neighboring Ukraine,﻿ the first time it has taken such a step i﻿n what is a major provocation for Europe and NATO. 

Addressing the country’s parliament, Poland’s Prime Minister Donald Tusk said there were 19 intrusions of its airspace, and that a “large proportion” of the drones entered it from Belarus. #CNN #News
title: Poland shoots down Russian drones in its airspace for the first time

author: CNN
description: A heated debate is erupting on Capitol Hill over accusations that the Trump administration committed a “war crime” after an unprecedented strike on a boat in international waters. The White House says they were targeting a Venezuelan gang bringing drugs into the US, but have failed to provide evidence to the public. #CNN #News
title: Ana Navarro on Trump war crime concerns: His actions are 'schizophrenic'

author: CNN
description: Protests in Nepal's capital Kathmandu were initially triggered by a ban on social media, but quickly expanded to include issues of wider corruption, lack of economic opportunities and police violence against demonstrators. CNN's Kristie Lu Stout breaks down the so-called "Gen Z" protests that has seen young people criticize "nepo babies," or entitled children of government officials. #cnn #news #nepal #protests
title: Nepal’s protests aren’t just about social media

author: CNN
description: Donald Trump has repeatedly expressed his disappointment with Russian President Vladimir Putin and the ongoing Ukraine war over several months. CNN's Abby Philip, however, points out his rhetoric might contradict his actions.
title: Abby Phillip: Is Trump actually 'not happy' with Putin?

author: CNN
description: CNN's Erin Burnett talks with Rep. Robert Garcia about his response to Rep. James Comer calling him a "drama queen."
title: ‘Clearly saying that because I’m gay’: Garcia responds to Comer ‘queen’ dig

author: CNN
description:
As Trump was sitting down to dine, he was approached by protesters chanting “Free DC” and “Free Palestine.”

In video obtained by CNN, a handful of protesters begin chanting, “Free DC, free Palestine, Trump is the Hitler of our time” as the president makes his way through the dining room. The protesters are booed by others dining in the restaurant, and the president ultimately came within a few feet of the protesters before the video ends. #CNN #News
title: 'Free DC, free Palestine': Protesters confront Trump as he dines in DC

author: CNN
description:
Israel on Tuesday ordered a complete evacuation of Gaza City, home to around a million Palestinians, ahead of its controversial military takeover.

“To all residents of Gaza City and all its neighborhoods, from the Old City and Tuffah in the east to the sea in the west. The IDF is determined to defeat Hamas and will operate in the Gaza City area with great force, just as it did throughout the Strip,” Avichay Adraee, the military’s Arabic spokesperson said on Tuesday. #CNN #News
title: 'This is only the beginning': Netanyahu's warning as full evacuation of Gaza City ordered

author: CNN
description: CNN's Erin Burnett sits down with Maryland Governor Wes Moore to discuss Trump's threat to send the National Guard to Baltimore, announcing his bid for reelection, and whether he would run for President in 2028. #CNN #News
title: Maryland Gov. Wes Moore on Trump crime crackdown, seeking reelection, and 2028 buzz

author: CNN
description: Sweden's new Health Minister, Elisabet Lann, collapsed on her first day of work while being introduced at a press conference. Lann says she collapsed due to low blood sugar.
title: Swedish health minister collapses on first day of work

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump said today he wouldn’t comment on a “birthday book,” released as part of the Jeffrey Epstein records by the House Oversight Committee, that included a note bearing his name. He called it a “dead issue.” #CNN #News
title: House expecting more Epstein documents as WH calls it a 'hoax'
